item.title: European Union supports Egypt in collaboration with UNICEF to improve workforce performance in inclusive primary schools
item.dc:creator: root
item.content:encoded: CAIRO, 28 May 2018 - The European Union (EU) and the Government of Egypt (GoE), represented by the Ministry of Education (MoE), and the Alexandria Governorate in collaboration with the United Nations Childrens Fund (UNICEF) celebrated today the inauguration of the first group of inclusive schools in the context of the programme Expanding Access to Education and Protection for at Risk Children in Egypt.

item.title: EU tops up funding for UNICEF to help children affected by humanitarian crises
item.dc:creator: root
item.content:encoded: MOGADISHU, 17 July 2018 The European Union (EU) is contributing an additional 5 million in humanitarian support, towards UNICEFs response, which will provide lifesaving health, nutrition, water, sanitation, education and protection services to children caught in the ongoing crisis in Somalia.
